---
description: Detector implementation pattern
globs: ["src/detectors/**", "src/harness/**", "src/types.ts"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Every detector:

- Lives at `src/detectors/<category>/<rule-id>.ts`, one rule per file.
- Exports a `const` implementing the `Detector` interface from
  `src/types.ts`: `{ id, category, run(input: DetectorInput): Finding[] }`.
- `run` is pure: no network access, no filesystem access beyond `input`, no
  global state. Anything a detector needs beyond the file's content goes
  through `input.meta`.
- Is registered in `src/detectors/index.ts`.

Use `src/detectors/type-anesthesia/as-any-cast.ts` and
`src/detectors/phantom-dependency/unresolved-import.ts` as the reference
implementations — same shape, same use of the TypeScript AST via
`ts.createSourceFile` + `ts.forEachChild`, same `meta`-driven severity
tagging.

Prefer AST traversal over regex for anything with a syntax tree (casts,
imports, catch blocks, declarations). Regex is acceptable for genuinely
textual signals (e.g. scanning comment text for keywords like "ensure" /
"guarantee").

After any change: run `npm test`. Read the full report, not just the
fixtures for the category you're working on — a new detector firing on an
existing fixture is a false positive that needs fixing before the category
is done.
